      • canModifyComment

        public boolean canModifyComment(SimplePageComment c,
                       boolean canEditPage)
        Admins can always edit. Authors can edit for 30 minutes. The second parameter is only used to distinguish this method from the one directly below it. Allowing CommentsProducer to cache whether or not the current user can edit the page, without having to hit the database each time.

      • deleteComment

        public String deleteComment(String commentUUID)
        Comments aren't actually deleted. The comment field is set to empty. This is so that the namings remain consistent when the comment section is set to show names as anonymous. Otherwise, deleting a post could change the numbering, which hinders discussion.

      • getAvailableCss

        public ArrayList<ContentResource> getAvailableCss()
        Returns an ArrayList containing all of the system-wide and site-wide CSS files. One entry may be null, to separate system-wide from site-wide. Caches lookups, to prevent extra database hits.

      • getCssForCurrentPage

        public ContentResource getCssForCurrentPage()
        First checks if a sheet has been explicitly set. Then checks for a default at the site level. It then finally checks to see if there is a default on the system level. Caches lookups to prevent too many lookups in the database.
